Interface DisjunctiveRelation<T extends BaseRelation>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, Relation, Visitable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AlgebraRelation<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    A16AlgebraRelation, A2AlgebraRelation, A5AlgebraRelation, BitSetAlgebraRelation, BitSetDisjunctiveRelation

    public interface DisjunctiveRelation<T extends BaseRelation>
extends Relation, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Represents a dijunctive ontology alignment relation. A disjunctive ontology alignment relation is made of the disjunction of several atomic relations. This disjunction is traditionally represented as a set. This allows for the natural implementation of the conjunction and disjunction operation.
